<subSubSection pageNumber="625" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="625">
Conserved type (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jørgensen">Jorgensen</normalizedToken>
&amp; al. in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="625">Taxon</emphasis>
43: 651. 1994): Italy. Trentino, Cortina 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Ampezzo">d'Ampezzo</normalizedToken>
, Pocol, 1948, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="625">G. Degelius</emphasis>
(UPS).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageNumber="625" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="625">
Current name: 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Weber ex F. H. Wigg." authorityName="F. H. Wigg." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Goodeniaceae" genus="Collema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cristatum">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageNumber="625">Collema cristatum</emphasis>
(L.) Weber ex F.H. Wigg.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zenker" authorityYear="1827" rank="family">Collemataceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageNumber="625" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="625">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="625">Note:</emphasis>
Degelius (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="625">Symb. Bot. Upsal.</emphasis>
13(2): 308. 1954) designated a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
(contrary to Art. 9.11 because original material, the Dillenius figure, was in existence). The latter was the sole available element and was therefore designated as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, along with an 
<typeStatus>epitype</typeStatus>
, by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jørgensen">Jorgensen</normalizedToken>
&amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="625">Bot. J. Linn. Soc.</emphasis>
115: 299. 1994). Unfortunately, the type belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sw.) Ach." authorityName="Ach." baseAuthorityName="Sw." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Goodeniaceae" genus="Collema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenax">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="625">Collema tenax</emphasis>
(Sw.) Ach.
</taxonomicName>
, so these authors successfully proposed the conservation of the name with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Degelius’">Degelius'</normalizedToken>
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
as the conserved type.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
